Mohammed VI, the king of unfinished reforms
description: 'The Enigma of Mohammed VI' (3/6). The Moroccan king's coronation in 1999 sparked great hope at home and abroad. After the reign of his father, which was marked by human rights abuses, the young monarch personified change and modernity, at least at the beginning.

description: More than 20 people died on Monday, among them medical staff and five journalists. Benjamin Netanyahu was forced to express his regrets, while the Israeli military cited collateral damage. Yet the use of a 'double strike,' a tactic repeatedly employed since the start of the war, undermines that argument.

headline: France to sue Kick platform for 'negligence' after livestream death
description: Raphael Graven, known online as 'Jean Pormanove' or 'JP,' died after a 12-day live-streaming marathon on his channel, which specialized in him enduring abuse or humiliation dished out by other participants.

description: 'May '68 Thinkers Reflect On Trump Era' (1/6). The philosopher of emancipation examines the roots of the current reactionary offensive. He views contemporary utopian micro-communities as new ways of 'living as equals.'

Life in the West Bank settlement of Kedem Arava: 'We're not taking anyone's place, there is only sand around us'
description: Established in 2017 near the Jordanian border, the Kedem Arava settlement contains prefabricated homes housing some 60 families, former city dwellers seeking a life closer to nature. While most residents deny ideological motivation, their presence fully aligns with the annexation of Palestinian territory sought by the Israeli far right.

headline: Labubu craze leads to shortages and surge in counterfeits
description: Pop Mart, the Beijing-based company behind the collectible figurines, reports record half-year results but struggles to meet demand despite automating its factories.

headline: François Truffaut's obsession with Isabelle Adjani
description: 'Adjani, The Famous Stranger' (2/6). While making a name for herself at the Comédie Française, the young actress became the French filmmaker's obsession, who courted her insistently on the set of 'The Story of Adèle H.' in 1975. She resisted him and made her mark with a performance full of restrained violence.
